Other improvements to Oniro's security:

- implement musl + a hardened malloc library, like the one developed by the GrapheneOS Android distribution: https://github.com/GrapheneOS/hardened_malloc

- enable SELinux and write an appropriate sepolicy

- additional kernel hardening such as: https://github.com/anthraxx/linux-hardened

- disable password authentication in SSH and only allow key-based authentication

- install and run some kind of intrusion detection system such as Snort
